@node Pozadavky "Requirements"

@{"AutoRun" link Oprogramu} needs

  - min. @{B}OS 2.1@{UB} (@{I}should @{UI}work, but tested only @{B}OS 3.0@{UB} and @{B}3.1@{UB})


    That's all :-)


@endnode


@node Instalace "Instalation"

  - You can use the instalation utility or

  - install @{"AutoRun" link Oprogramu} by hands.
    Just copy @{"AutoRun" link Oprogramu} with icon to another drawer.
    Copy to @{B}Sys:WBStartup/@{UB} is recommemded.

@endnode


@node usage "Usage"
Usage of @{"AutoRun" link Oprogramu} is very simple. Just click on its icon to be @{"AutoRun" link Oprogramu}
active. If You want to quit @{"AutoRun" link Oprogramu} so you have two options.
The first - Double click on AutoRuns icon again or
the second - use the @{B}Exchange@{UB} Program

@{"AutoRun" link Oprogramu} check drive @{B}DF0:@{UB}. After inserting some diskette it looks for
the script named @{"Auto-StartUp" link autostartup} in the directory @{B}S@{UB} on the diskette.
If it exists then will be executed.
@endnode


@node AutoStartup "Auto-StartUp"
@{B}Auto-StartUp@{UB} is a normal script file like for example @{I}Startup-Sequence @{UI}
and must be saved in the directory @{B}S@{UB}
@endnode


@node tooltypes
in version 3.05 @{"AutoRun" link Oprogramu} Support only one tooltype

    @{B}CX_PRIORITY@{UB}     - Set the priority of commodity

you can also use the system tooltype

    @{B}DONOTWAIT@{UB}       - its necesary If you want to run @{"AutoRun" link Oprogramu} from
                      @{B}WBStartup@{UB}.
@endnode


